attributes.Description: Sparse vegetation due to recently clear cut within past ten years. Dead material covering forest floor. Primarily immature trees and disturbed forest.  Species encountered on transects: Pinus ponderosa(2), Calocedrus decurrens

Established mixed pine forest with underbrush. Some Oak trees present. Granite exposed. Adjacent to river and U.S. Route 50.  Species encountered on transects: Pinus ponderosa(2), Calocedrus decurrens
Healthy Lodgepole Pine and White Fir trees within mixed age forest. Species encountered on transects: Abies concolor (6)
Mature mixed pine forest forest. Species encountered on transects: Calocedrus decurrens
Mixed age pine forest with granite and manzanita brush. Species encountered on transects: Abies concolor, Pinus ponderosa, Calocedrus decurrens(3), Pinus jeffreyi
Barren rock immediately surrounding point of interest, sparse old growth trees in isolation. Area has been clear cut in recent time. Species encountered on transects: Pinus attenuata

Recently cleared area with mixed oak trees and pine forest remaining. Plenty of shrubs and grasses. Species encountered on transects: Quercus kelloggii, Calocedrus decurrens(4), Abies magnifica, Abies concolor

Young trees, second growth within the last seventy years. Dense pine immature trees competing for sunlight. Lots of exposed underbrush in immediate area. Species encountered on transects: Pseudotsuga menziesii, Calocedrus decurrens
Mixed age pine forest with lots of underbrush. Species encountered on transects: Calocedrus decurrens, Pseudotsuga menziesii(2), Aegopodium podagraria
On top of ridge. Visible fire in recent history. Partial canopy fire leaving some trees standing among badly burned trees and hanging snags. Species encountered on transect: Abies concolor
Few old growth trees among dense younger, shorter pine and hardwood forest. Species encounter on transect: Calocedrus decurrens(3), Quercus kelloggii, Pinus lambertiana
Logged area, with small sugar pines and douglas fir pine trees. Species encountered on transect: Pseudotsuga menziesii
Brush and immature pine tree dominate with thick grove of manzanita covering the forest floor. Species encountered on transects: Pinus ponderosa(3)
Area devastated by total canopy fire. No growing trees in sight in any direction. Minor signs of brush regrowth showing.

Mixed Fir and pine forest with hardwoods. Borders clear cut area. Nearly half of land cover exposed ground. Species encountered on transect: Pinus ponderosa (3), Pinus contorta,  Calocedrus decurrens, Abies concolor
Point taken on beach extending far into the interior of Boone Lake Reservoir. Area exposed due to extreme drought. Granite rocks present with lack of vegetation.
In very remote region near Bear Lake Reservoir. Mixed age healthy forest with exposed granite and lots of exposed brush. Sign of stratified forest. No trees encountered on transects.

Captured at Salt Lake Springs Reservoir to demonstrate extreme drought. Water level well below normal levels allowing access to interior of reservoir. Near southern boundary of Eldorado National Forest boundary

Taken near fire station at intersection of Forest Service road and Route 88. Young pine forest primarily exposed soil. Area apparently disturbed by clear cutting and/ or insect or fire presence. Species encountered on transect: Abies magnifica
Above tree line along Pacific Coast Trail near eastern boundary of Eldorado National Forest. Little to no vegetation present including grass. Lots of rocks, not necessarily granite. No soil.
Regenerated pine forest with manzanita brush, pine needles, and deuterium covering forest floor. Species encountered on transects: Pinus ponderosa
Regenerated pine forest with manzanita brush, pine needles, and deuterium covering forest floor. Species encountered on transects: Pinus ponderosa
Mountain Hemlocks in valley by river bank. Lots of rocks and broadleaf trees present. Trees encountered on transect: Tsuga mertensiana
